abstract.gco:CharacterString: Statewide coverage of 1960 Places based on population data available from the U.S. Bureau of the Census. Population data is from the Eighteenth Decennial Census of the United States (1960 Census of Population)

purpose.gco:CharacterString: To use in GIS systems for historical study and analysis This datasets is made available to interested persons through the University of Arizona's instance of Open Geoportal. It has been provided to assist educators, students, researchers, and policy makers in mapping and/or analysis applications.

credit.gco:CharacterString: Chris Kollen, University of Arizona Library

title.gco:CharacterString: REQUIRED: Reference to a formally registered thesaurus or a similar authoritative source of theme keywords.

environmentDescription.gco:CharacterString: Microsoft Windows XP Version 5.1 (Build 2600) Service Pack 2; ESRI ArcCatalog 9.2.2.1350

measureDescription.gco:CharacterString: Digitized city boundaries from the following maps: Avondale, Buckeye, Chandler, El Mirage, Gila Bend, Gilbert, Glendale, Goodyear, Mesa, Peoria, Phoenix, Scottsdale, Tempe, Tolleson, and Wickenburg used Maricopa County Annexation File; Benson used Benson 15' topographic quadrangle, 1958; Bisbee used Street map of the Bisbee area, Bisbee, Arizona, Arizona's copper capital, 1960; Casa Grande used General map: City of Casa Grande, 1963; Clarkdale used Map of Area for Annexation to townsite of Clarkdale Yavapai County, Arizona, 1960; Clifton used Map of Greenlee County, 1916 (no changes until 1970); Coolidge, Eloy, and Florence used Street map of... Florence, Coolidge, Eloy, and romantic Pinal County, 1959; Douglas used City of Douglas, 1962; Duncan used Atlas of Greenlee County, 1965; Flagstaff used City of Flagstaff, a planning and zoning map for annexation; Globe and Winkleman used Atlas of Gila County, 1961; Hayden used Official map of Hayden Town, 1964; Holbrook used Holbrook, Arizona 196-; Huachuca City used Atlas of Cochise County, 1966; Kearny used Kearny 7.5' topographic quadrangle, 1964; Kingman used Map of city of Kingman, 196-; Mammoth used Atlas of Pinal County, 1964; Miami used Street Map of the Town of Miami, 1958; Nogales and Patagonia used Atlas of Santa Cruz County, 1961; Parker used Plot of the Townsite of Parker, 1956; Pima used Thatcher 15' topographic quadrangle, 1960; Prescott used City of Prescott Annexation History, 2007; Safford used City of Safford. 1964; Sierra Vista used Base map for planning Sierra Vista planning area, 1963; Snowflake used Street map of Snowflake, 196-; Somerton used City of Somerton Annexation map; South Tucson and Tucson used Tucson Annexation Boundary File; Thatcher used Thatcher, Arizona, Graham Co. Water distribution system with minimum improvements, 1958; West Yuma used Arizona minor civil divisions--supervisorial districts, 1950; Willcox used Willcox, 1956; Williams used Map of city of Williams, Arizona, compiled from plats, records, and original surveys, 1959; Winslow used Map of the City of Winslow, 1961; and Yuma used City of Yuma Annexation map. For remaining places, used Geographic Names Information System database for point data. Created a 200 meter buffer around all point data in order to convert into polygons.

value.gco:Record: Accuracy ranges from ~10 meters (Scale 1:1,008) to ~75 meters (Scale 1:63,360)

description.gco:CharacterString: Dataset renamed from 1960_Cities.shp to Arizona_CensusPlaces_1960.shp by Ben Hickson with the University of Arizona Library.
